The Federal Government has pledged $12 million to the Global Fund to tackle HIV, tuberculosis and malaria. A statement from the National Agency for the Control of AIDS yesterday said Nigeria made the commitment  during  the  sixth replenishment conference of the Global Fund to Fight AIDS, Tuberculosis and Malaria (Global Fund), in France. The conference brought together leaders from all over the world. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY The amount pledged was a 20% increase from previous amounts. The government also said it was committed to increasing domestic resources for health and disease programmes.  HIV/AIDS: FG reaffirms commitment to Global Fund Nigeria receives $225m grant for HIV, TB, malaria Nigeria and Domestic Financing for Health